{
  "texts": [
    "'Pretrained' refers to the extensive amounts of data it has been trained on to do next word prediction.",
    "'Transformer' refers to aspects of the neural network architecture (Radford et al., 2018).",
    "In particular, we compared the performance of GPT-3.5, as implemented in the OpenAI API as gpt-3.5-turbo, and GPT-4, as implemented in the OpenAI API as gpt-4.",
    "GPT-3.5 is freely available via ChatGPT, while GPT-4 can be accessed via the API or the paid version of ChatGPT.",
    "We utilized six prompt approaches: base, bare bones, chain-of-thought, persona, vocalize and reflect, and method explained."
  ]
}